mpios.description: The process and memory information of MP2600 infomation!

EnabledStatus.name: EnabledStatus
EnabledStatus.description: A simple status value for the object.

numBytesFree.name: numBytesFree
numBytesFree.description: The number of bytes free in the system memory

numBlocksFree.name: numBlocksFree
numBlocksFree.description: The number of blocks free in the system memory

avgBlockSizeFree.name: avgBlockSizeFree
avgBlockSizeFree.description: The average block size that is free in the system memory

maxBlockSizeFree.name: maxBlockSizeFree
maxBlockSizeFree.description: The largest block size that is free in the memory

numBytesAlloc.name: numBytesAlloc
numBytesAlloc.description: The number of bytes of system memory that have been allocated by tasks and system services

numBlocksAlloc.name: numBlocksAlloc
numBlocksAlloc.description: The number of blocks of system memory that have been allocated in the system

avgBlockSizeAlloc.name: avgBlockSizeAlloc
avgBlockSizeAlloc.description: The average memory block size that has been allocated in the system

allocBytesPercent.name: allocBytesPercent
allocBytesPercent.description: The allocated bytes percent which value is allocated bytes divided by total bytes, This value can be in the range from 0 to 100.

taskTable.name: taskTable
taskTable.description: Represents the target's task table. Each entry in this table represents a task

taskEntry.name: taskEntry
taskEntry.description: Each entry contains information with regards to a task in the system

taskId.name: taskId
taskId.description: This is the task ID assigned by VxWorks to a task in the system. A taskId of zero specifies a new task.

taskName.name: taskName
taskName.description: This is the name of the VxWorks task. This value can only be specified (set) at task creation.

taskPriority.name: taskPriority
taskPriority.description: The priority of the VxWorks task. This value can be in the range from 0, the highest priority, to 255, the lowest priority.

taskStatus.name: taskStatus
taskStatus.description: This field specifies the current task status. It can be used to change the current task state. For example, to suspend a task, the value of taskStatus is changed to task-suspended, to delete a task the value is changed to task-deleted, etc...

taskOptions.name: taskOptions
taskOptions.description: This value represents the sum of the following options: value option 1 VX_SUPERVISOR_MODE(read-only) 2 VX_UNBREAKABLE (break points ignored) 4 VX_DEALLOC_STACK (deallocate stack) 8 VX_FP_TASK (floating point support) 16 VX_STDIO (read-only) 128 VX_PRIVATE_ENV (private env. variables) 256 VX_NO_STACK_FILL (don't fill stack) All the options above can be set at task creation time. However, once the task is executing the only option that can be changed is VX_UNBREAKABLE. The option is toggled based on the current setting.

taskMain.name: taskMain
taskMain.description: This is the name of the entry function for the VxWorks task. This name can only be specified when a task is created (entry added in the table). The symbol must exist in the VxWorks target.

taskStackPtr.name: taskStackPtr
taskStackPtr.description: This is the saved stack pointer for the task.

taskStackBase.name: taskStackBase
taskStackBase.description: This is the address of the bottom of the stack of the VxWorks task.

taskStackPos.name: taskStackPos
taskStackPos.description: This is the effective top of the stack in the current task state.

taskStackEnd.name: taskStackEnd
taskStackEnd.description: This is the address of the top of the stack of the VxWorks task.

taskStackSize.name: taskStackSize
taskStackSize.description: This is the actual size of the stack in bytes. The size of the stack can only be specified at task creation (adding an entry to the table).

taskStackSizeUsage.name: taskStackSizeUsage
taskStackSizeUsage.description: The number of bytes currently in use by the task from the stack.

taskStackMaxUsed.name: taskStackMaxUsed
taskStackMaxUsed.description: This is the maximum number of bytes that have been used by the task from the stack.

taskStackFree.name: taskStackFree
taskStackFree.description: This is the number of bytes that are free currently in the task stack.

taskErrorStatus.name: taskErrorStatus
taskErrorStatus.description: This is the most recent error status for this task.

taskDescr.name: taskDescr
taskDescr.description: This is description for error task. If the task runs well the string will be null.

sysCpuStatus.name: sysCpuStatus
sysCpuStatus.description: This is the status of collecting CPU utilization rate which include two status: spyCpu (2), noSpyCpu(1), if you want to get cpuUtilTable and cpuTaskTable, you must make status to spy cpu

sysCpuTaskTabView.name: sysCpuTaskTabView
sysCpuTaskTabView.description: This is the status of cpuTaskTable view: detailed view is showing every task info and simple view is only showing task which had used cpu

checkCpuTimeInterval.name: checkCpuTimeInterval
checkCpuTimeInterval.description: check cpu time interval,unit is second

cpuTaskTable.name: cpuTaskTable
cpuTaskTable.description: Represents the target's task cpu table. Each entry in this table represents a task

cpuTaskEntry.name: cpuTaskEntry
cpuTaskEntry.description: Each entry contains information with regards to a task cpu in the system

cpuTaskId.name: cpuTaskId
cpuTaskId.description: This is the task ID assigned by VxWorks to a task in the system. A taskId of zero specifies a new task.

cpuTaskName.name: cpuTaskName
cpuTaskName.description: This is the name of the VxWorks task. This value can only be specified (set) at task creation.

cpuTaskPri.name: cpuTaskPri
cpuTaskPri.description: The priority of the VxWorks task. This value can be in the range from 0, the highest priority, to 255, the lowest priority.

cpuTaskDeltaUtil.name: cpuTaskDeltaUtil
cpuTaskDeltaUtil.description: The CPU utilization of the VxWorks task during DeltaTicks. This value can be in the range from 0 to 100.

cpuTaskDeltaTicks.name: cpuTaskDeltaTicks
cpuTaskDeltaTicks.description: The task CPU utilization delta ticks.

cpuTaskAverageUtil.name: cpuTaskAverageUtil
cpuTaskAverageUtil.description: The CPU utilization of the VxWorks task during TotalTicks. This value can be in the range from 0 to 100.

cpuTaskTotalTicks.name: cpuTaskTotalTicks
cpuTaskTotalTicks.description: The total ticks till cpuTaskStatus been start, until the status be end.

cpuUtilTable.name: cpuUtilTable
cpuUtilTable.description: The Sys CPU total utilization table

cpuUtilEntry.name: cpuUtilEntry
cpuUtilEntry.description: The Sys CPU utilization table at a certain period of time, include two kind of time interval: one is from spy cpu to current show cpu, the other is from last show cpu to current show cpu

cpuUtilDeltaUtil.name: cpuUtilDeltaUtil
cpuUtilDeltaUtil.description: The Sys CPU utilization in delta times

cpuUtilDeltaUsedTicks.name: cpuUtilDeltaUsedTicks
cpuUtilDeltaUsedTicks.description: The System used ticks in delta ticks

cpuUtilDeltaTicks.name: cpuUtilDeltaTicks
cpuUtilDeltaTicks.description: The Sys CPU utilization ticks in delta times

cpuUtilDeltaTimes.name: cpuUtilDeltaTimes
cpuUtilDeltaTimes.description: The delta times, unit is second

cpuUtilAverageUtil.name: cpuUtilAverageUtil
cpuUtilAverageUtil.description: The Sys CPU utilization in total times

cpuUtilTotalUsedTicks.name: cpuUtilTotalUsedTicks
cpuUtilTotalUsedTicks.description: The Sys CPU utilization used ticks in total times

cpuUtilTotalTicks.name: cpuUtilTotalTicks
cpuUtilTotalTicks.description: The Sys CPU utilization ticks in total times

cpuUtilTotalTimes.name: cpuUtilTotalTimes
cpuUtilTotalTimes.description: The total times, unit is second

sysCpuTemper.name: sysCpuTemper
sysCpuTemper.description: Get current system environment cpu temperature

sysCpuAlertTemper.name: sysCpuAlertTemper
sysCpuAlertTemper.description: Get or set current system environment cpu alarm temperature default is 85 C

sysMainBoardTemper.name: sysMainBoardTemper
sysMainBoardTemper.description: Get current system environment main borad temperature

sysMainBoardAlertTemper.name: sysMainBoardAlertTemper
sysMainBoardAlertTemper.description: Get or set current system environment main board alarm temperature default is 65 C

sysAlertTrapInt.name: sysAlertTrapInt
sysAlertTrapInt.description: Send alert trap time interval when system temperature is always more than alert temperature, unit is second,default is 60 s

sysRtrCtrl.name: sysRtrCtrl
sysRtrCtrl.description: RTR global switch enable--enable RTR module disable--no RTR module

sysRtrResponder.name: sysRtrResponder
sysRtrResponder.description: Rtr Responder TRUE--Rtr Responder False--no Rtr Responder on valid in jitter entity now

sysRtrEntityTable.name: sysRtrEntityTable
sysRtrEntityTable.description: Rtr entity table,config or view information about Rtr entity

sysRtrEntityEntry.name: sysRtrEntityEntry
sysRtrEntityEntry.description: Rtr entity,config or view information about Rtr entity

rtrEntityLogType.name: rtrEntityLogType
rtrEntityLogType.description: RTR entity logging type local -stored in the device file system remote -remote services

rtrEntityLogMaxSize.name: rtrEntityLogMaxSize
rtrEntityLogMaxSize.description: rtr entity's log with max lines, if log type is local

rtrEntityThreshold.name: rtrEntityThreshold
rtrEntityThreshold.description: RTR entity log filter threshhod,only valid with icmpEcho entity

rtrGroupEntityMembers.name: rtrGroupEntityMembers
rtrGroupEntityMembers.description: RTR group members string type 1 3 10-20 50 string length no more than 255, separated by comma,no space in the string

rtrScheduleObjId.name: rtrScheduleObjId
rtrScheduleObjId.description: id of rtrschedule object which means rtr group or entity.

rtrScheduleStartTimeFlag.name: rtrScheduleStartTimeFlag
rtrScheduleStartTimeFlag.description: RTR schedule start time startNow >> afterTime >> startTime--start at the given time

rtrScheduleAfterTime.name: rtrScheduleAfterTime
rtrScheduleAfterTime.description: RTR schedule given time type string HH:MM:SS valid when sysRtrScheduleFlag is afterTime +/-.

rtrScheduleStartTime.name: rtrScheduleStartTime
rtrScheduleStartTime.description: RTR schedule given time type string HH:MM:SS,mm,dd,yyyy valid when sysRtrScheduleFlag is startTime.

rtrScheduleAgeOut.name: rtrScheduleAgeOut
rtrScheduleAgeOut.description: rtr schedule ageout time in second.

rtrScheduleLifeFlag.name: rtrScheduleLifeFlag
rtrScheduleLifeFlag.description: rtr schedule's life forever,if config, no need to config lifetime and repeat times repeatAndDie,if config, need to config lifetime and repeat times

rtrScheduleLifeTime.name: rtrScheduleLifeTime
rtrScheduleLifeTime.description: rtr schedule's lieftime in second, valid only when rtrScheduleLifeFlag is repeatAndDie.

rtrScheduleRepeat.name: rtrScheduleRepeat
rtrScheduleRepeat.description: rtr schedule's repeat times, valid only when rtrScheduleLifeFlag is repeatAndDie.

rtrIcmpEchoSourceIp.name: rtrIcmpEchoSourceIp

rtrIcmpEchoTos.name: rtrIcmpEchoTos
rtrIcmpEchoTos.description: ICMP TOS value, valid only rtrIcmpEchoExtendFlag is TRUE.

rtrIcmpEchoSetDf.name: rtrIcmpEchoSetDf

rtrIcmpEchoVerifyData.name: rtrIcmpEchoVerifyData

rtrIcmpEchoPktTotalSend.name: rtrIcmpEchoPktTotalSend

rtrIcmpEchoPktTotalRcvd.name: rtrIcmpEchoPktTotalRcvd
rtrIcmpEchoPktTotalRcvd.description: total packets which receive by the ICMP entity.

rtrJitterCodec.description: JITTER codec type,including: 1 G711MULAW,2 G711ALAW,3 G729A,4 USER_DEFINED 5 UNKOWN

rtrJitterMinRtt.name: rtrJitterMinRtt

sysIfPktPriStaTable.name: sysIfPktPriStaTable
sysIfPktPriStaTable.description: The statistics of interface's flow based on the precedence of IP packet. The index of this table is priority and ifIndex

sysIfPktPriStaEntry.name: sysIfPktPriStaEntry
sysIfPktPriStaEntry.description: The statistics of interface's flow based on the precedence of IP packet. The index of this table is priority and ifIndex

sysIfPktPriority.name: sysIfPktPriority
sysIfPktPriority.description: The precedence of IP packet, it start from 1 to 9. Numeric one represent the precedence 0, two represent 1 and so on. 9 represent the number of non-IP packet.

sysIfIndex.name: sysIfIndex
sysIfIndex.description: The index of interface in the system

sysIfDesc.name: sysIfDesc
sysIfDesc.description: The name of interface assigned to

sysIfInOctets.name: sysIfInOctets
sysIfInOctets.description: The interface received bytes at specified precedence

sysIfInUcastPkts.name: sysIfInUcastPkts
sysIfInUcastPkts.description: The number of subnetwork-unicast packets delivered to a higher-layer protocol with specified precedence.

sysIfInNUcastPkts.name: sysIfInNUcastPkts
sysIfInNUcastPkts.description: The number of non-unicast (i.e., subnetwork- broadcast or subnetwork-multicast) packets delivered to a higher-layer protocol.

sysIfInDiscards.name: sysIfInDiscards
sysIfInDiscards.description: The number of inbound packets which were chosen to be discarded

sysIfInErrors.name: sysIfInErrors
sysIfInErrors.description: The number of inbound packets that contained errors preventing them from being deliverable to a higher-layer protocol.

sysIfInUnkownProtos.name: sysIfInUnkownProtos
sysIfInUnkownProtos.description: The number of packets received via the interface which were discarded because of an unknown or unsupported protocol.

sysIfOutOctets.name: sysIfOutOctets
sysIfOutOctets.description: The total number of octets transmitted out of the interface, including framing characters.

sysIfOutUcastPkts.name: sysIfOutUcastPkts
sysIfOutUcastPkts.description: The total number of packets that higher-level protocols requested be transmitted to a subnetwork-unicast address, including those that were discarded or not sent.

sysIfOutNUcastPkts.name: sysIfOutNUcastPkts
sysIfOutNUcastPkts.description: The total number of packets that higher-level protocols requested be transmitted to a non- unicast (i.e., a subnetwork-broadcast or subnetwork-multicast) address, including those that were discarded or not sent.

sysIfOutDiscards.name: sysIfOutDiscards
sysIfOutDiscards.description: The number of outbound packets which were chosen to be even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being transmitted. One possible reason for discarding such a packet could be to free up buffer space.

sysIfOutErrors.name: sysIfOutErrors
sysIfOutErrors.description: The number of outbound packets that could not be transmitted because of errors.
